data.name: Settings_BufferSize_Explanation
data.value: The recording buffer is a memory cache. When disk I/O is fast, the buffer absorbs performance variation, and a small buffer may suffice. When disk I/O is limited, the buffer holds data as the I/O attempts to keep up with the incoming data. Once the buffer fills, incoming data is discarded. By extending the size of the buffer you can extend the available recording time before data is discarded. Doing so reduces the available memory for other running applications which may impact their performance.
